BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NfR0neqb9hUX5xLTfnAcT
SUMMARY:Medusa Quartet - genre-defying chamber-folk ensemble
DTSTAMP:20260406T013620Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T193000
DESCRIPTION:Named after one of mythology’s most misunderstood figures\\\, t
	he Medusa Quartet channels the power of transformation\\\, reclaiming what
	 was once feared and turning it into something fiercely magical. Saskia To
	mkins – Violin\\\, Viola\\\, Cello\\\, Nyckelharpa\; Marta Solek – Suka\\\
	, Plock Fiddle\\\, Cello\; Lea Kirstein – Violin\\\, Viola\\\, Cello\; Geo
	rgia Hathaway – Violin\\\, Vocals – A genre-defying chamber-folk quartet t
	hat fuses centuries-old string traditions with contemporary storytelling a
	nd original compositions.  Medusa’s dynamic arrangement style cross-pollin
	ates the sounds of Middle Eastern\\\, Scandinavian\\\, Celtic\\\, Appalach
	ian\\\, and Eastern European music\\\, as well as original tunes\\\, to cr
	eate something previously unheard. The dynamic band connects audiences acr
	oss dividing lines of culture and identity to reveal the common threads be
	neath. Join us for a very special concert! \\nDoors open at 6:30 pm for th
	e 7:00 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (lower Brick Buil
	ding). \\nTickets are available in advance online\\\, in-person at prior S
	FS concerts\\\, or at the door.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/med
	usa-quartet-genre-defying-chamber-folk-ensemble/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborh
	ood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/medusa-quartet-genre-defying-chambe
	r-folk-ensemble/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
